{"type":"message","id":"405a4b3d","parentId":"03fc977b","timestamp":"2026-03-20T14:08:29.838Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Planning the security audit**\n\nI think it's important to perform a health check since the user asked for an \"OpenClaw security audit.\" I should load the health check skill and outline a plan. This could involve checking the firewall, SSH, and conducting a basic security audit for OpenClaw, including updated packages, user file permissions, and access controls. I can propose running non-destructive commands to outline the steps needed for a lightweight audit, such as checking versions and running services.**Requesting permission to proceed**\n\nI'm thinking it might be a good idea to propose a structured report for the user. I should clearly lay out the plan and then ask for permission to move forward with the proposed actions. For now, I won't make any tool calls just yet. I want to make sure the user feels involved in the process and understands what's coming next, so a clear and direct communication will be key here.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"I can run a quick security audit focused on the OpenClaw setup here. I’ll keep it non-destructive and provide actionable results. Here’s the plan and what I can check right away:\n\nWhat I’ll audit\n- Environment and versioning\n  - Check OpenClaw version (if available in this workspace) and Node.js version\n  - Confirm the primary model and aliases are as configured (session scope)\n- Access and permissions\n  - Verify who can read/write workspace files (workspace/ and memory/ files)\n  - Look for overly permissive file modes (e.g., world-writable)\n- Heartbeat and scheduling\n  - Ensure HEARTBEAT.md is present and only has tasks you intend (no accidental exposure)\n- Data exposure risk\n  - Scan MEMORY.md and related files for sensitive data (PII, tokens) and suggest redactions\n- Running services and network exposure\n  - Check for any open ports or listening services in this environment (non-destructive checks)\n- Software hygiene\n  - Check for outdated dependencies referenced in the workspace (if detectable)\n  - Confirm backup/restore posture for critical files (memory/, MEMORY.md)\n\nQuestions to tailor the audit\n- Do you want me to run these checks now and generate a concise report, or would you prefer a staged plan with commands you can run locally?\n- Any particular threat model or assets to focus on (e.g., SSH access, remote API exposure, API keys in memory)?\n\nIf you’d like me to proceed, I can start with a non-destructive local audit and return:\n- A short risk score\n- Identified issues with suggested remediations\n- A minimal remediation plan you can apply\n\nShall I start the audit now?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/auto","usage":{"input":405,"output":780,"cacheRead":10496,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":11681,"cost":{"input":-405,"output":-780,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":-1185}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774015701405}}
